Package com.ivj.squirrelgame.entity

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BadBeast
    This entity attacks the player and gives him damage, moves only every 4th move
    BadPlant
    This entity stands still and gives the player damage
    DynamicEntity
    Abstract class for entities which don't move
    Entity
    Abstract class defining a entity for the game with a ID, a energy and a position
    EntitySet
    Container for saving Entities, implemented using ConcurrentHashMap
    GoodBeast
    This entity runs away from the player and gives him energy, moves only every 4th move
    GoodPlant
    This entity stands still and gives the player energy
    HandOperatedMasterSquirrel
    This entity is like a MasterSquirrel but can be operated from outside e.g by the player
    MasterSquirrel
    This entity is a playable entity which collects energy
    MasterSquirrelBot
    This entity is a playable entity which collects energy and is controlled by AI
    MiniSquirrel
    This entity collects energy but is not directly playable.
    MiniSquirrelBot
    This entity is like MiniSquirrel, but movement is implemented using AI
    StandardMiniSquirrel
    This entity is like MiniSquirrel, but movement is implemented by choosing random direction
    StaticEntity
    Abstract class for entities which are moving
    Wall
    This entity stands still and gives the player damage on collision
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EntitySetException
    General purpose exception used by EntitySet and related
    NotEnoughEnergyException
    Exception thrown on trying to spawn a MiniSquirrel or derivations of it with not enough energy
